{
  "stem": "19198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 224.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] What I remember most is that of those nine or 10 days that we spent on the ship, four or five were a terrible, terrible storm, which I spent flat on my-- on my back, except for the times when I had to bend over the-- the side of the bed and get rid of what little I had eaten.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were five of us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, of course.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the-- the big-- the big riddle of the future, the-- I'm-- don't know about the others, but I had never heard of the Hebrew Union College until I learned about this opportunity.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, we felt that Americans probably knew very little about Judaism.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We learned that several of the-- of the teachers at the Hebrew Union College had done their graduate work in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- we still felt very much part of-- of those families, if-- if that's what you mean by what we left behind.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Obviously our major, if not sole, contact with Germany from that moment on were our families.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what happened to them was very much of a concern to-- to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- if I'm not going too far ahead, the-- when we had news of Kristallnacht--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Vaguely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Vaguely, perhaps.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We're-- if we thought theoretically, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But by that time our-- we had not been affected in any essential way by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The life for Jews had become far more uncomfortable.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we knew that there-- there was a-- a-- some-- some danger, but we-- we were not as conscious of the radical nature of the danger as apparently were some more farsighted Americans who were wise enough to want to-- to start take people out of Germany and give them a chance for survival.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
